    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-vr-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Single-point hemolysis validation at nominal operating condition",
      "description": "Validation was performed using one experimental measurement at the nominal pump operating point (flow rate Q = 5 L/min, rotational speed N = 2400 RPM). The CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH = 0.81) agreed with the single experimental measurement (RH_exp = 0.84) to within 3.6%. No replicate experiments were conducted; no statistical uncertainty bounds were computed. The remaining four flow-speed combinations specified in the COU (Q = 3 L/min / N = 2000 RPM; Q = 4 L/min / N = 2200 RPM; Q = 6 L/min / N = 2600 RPM; Q = 7 L/min / N = 2800 RPM) were not experimentally validated. The single data point at the nominal condition is taken as representative of model accuracy across the full operating envelope."
    }
